<subSubSection type="nomenclature">
<paragraph pageNumber="290">Types Naturhist. Mus. Wien.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="etymology">
<paragraph pageNumber="290">
Etymology L 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:33735" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole fallax Mayr" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole fallax Mayr" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="290" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fallax">fallax</taxonomicName>
, deceitful, false; allusion unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageNumber="290">
diagnosis A member of the 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:33735" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole fallax Mayr" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole fallax Mayr" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="290" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fallax">fallax</taxonomicName>
group, similar to 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:181731" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole gigas Wilson" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole gigas Wilson" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="290" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gigas">gigas</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:142274" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole jelskii Mayr" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole jelskii Mayr" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="290" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jelskii">jelskii</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:181813" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole obscurithorax Forel" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole obscurithorax Forel" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="290" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obscurithorax">obscurithorax</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:181822" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole puttemansi Forel" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole puttemansi Forel" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="290" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="puttemansi">puttemansi</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:181823" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole roushae Wilson" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole roushae Wilson" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="290" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="roushae">roushae</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:181829" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole tobini Wilson" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole tobini Wilson" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="290" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tobini">tobini</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:181831" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole valens Wilson" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole valens Wilson" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="290" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="valens">valens</taxonomicName>
, and especially the very abundant and widespread 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:142274" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole jelskii Mayr" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole jelskii Mayr" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="290" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jelskii">jelskii</taxonomicName>
, with which it is easily confused.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="description">
<paragraph pageNumber="290">Major: posterior half of dorsal surface of head primarily carinulate, with rugoreticulum extensive mesad of the eye most of the way to the occiput; pronotum transversely carinulate; anterior fourth to third of central strip of first gastral tergite shagreened; head tapered toward occiput in side view, as shown.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="290">
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:33735" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole fallax Mayr" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole fallax Mayr" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="290" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fallax">P. fallax</taxonomicName>
differs from 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:142274" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole jelskii Mayr" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole jelskii Mayr" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="290" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jelskii">P. jelskii</taxonomicName>
as follows and as depicted: in major, petiolar node higher and descending to peduncle by a much more concave curve, and scapes shorter (Scape Length/Head Width 0.50-0.59 as opposed to 0.60-0.70 in 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:142274" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole jelskii Mayr" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole jelskii Mayr" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="290" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jelskii">jelskii</taxonomicName>
major); and in minor, occiput much broader and nuchal collar thinner than in 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:142274" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole jelskii Mayr" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole jelskii Mayr" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="290" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jelskii">jelskii</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="290">Measurements (mm) Lectotype major: HW 1.72, HL 1.84, SL 0.90, EL 0.24, PW 0.80. Paralectotype minor: HW 0.60, HL 0.72, SL 0.92, EL 0.18, PW 0.40.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageNumber="290">Color Major and minor: body medium reddish brown, with gaster sometimes dark reddish brown.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="distribution">
<paragraph pageNumber="290">
Range A circum-Caribbean species, which I have verified from the Greater Antilles (Cuba, Jamaica, Puerto Rico), Central America, Colombia, and Venezuela. No certain records exist from the Lesser Antilles, where the closely related 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:142274" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole jelskii Mayr" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole jelskii Mayr" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="290" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jelskii">jelskii</taxonomicName>
abounds.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph pageNumber="290">
Biology Because 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:33735" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole fallax Mayr" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole fallax Mayr" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="290" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fallax">fallax</taxonomicName>
has a range enclosed by the more abundant 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:142274" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole jelskii Mayr" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole jelskii Mayr" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="290" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jelskii">jelskii</taxonomicName>
and is so easily confused with it, natural history notes published in the past under the name of either species are generally unreliable.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection type="materials_examined">
<paragraph pageNumber="290">
Figure Upper: major (compared with lectotype); variation in hypostomal teeth shown is with specimens from Puerto Rico (4 teeth) and Cuba (3 teeth). Lower: minor (compared with paralectotype, which shares the long, thin propodeal spine depicted; the very short spine at the top is of a Panama specimen, and the medium-length spine in the middle is of a syntype of the synonymous &quot; 
<taxonomicName LSID-HNS="urn:lsid:biosci.ohio-state.edu:osuc_concepts:188644" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Pheidole" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Pheidole jelskii var. columbica" lsidName-HNS="Pheidole columbica Forel" order="Hymenoptera" pageNumber="290" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="variety" species="jelskii" variety="columbica">var. columbica</taxonomicName>
&quot;). CUBA: Soledad, Las Villas. (Type locality: Cuba.) Scale bars = 1 mm.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
